Text: W-Winner...Mundane Mann!
What the hell is going on here...

He took out Goldy the Unbeaten Legend yesterday,
and now he snags another win today. That means
he's headed to the main tourney.

Quinton may not've been the flashiest fighter, but he
was reliably strong and the odds were in his favor.
Not the type of guy you'd expect to get completely
shut down.

You don't make it this far on lucky breaks alone, but
I haven't the faintest what this Mundane guy's trick
is... I can't figure out if he's a good bet or not...

Sounds like a fun dark horse bet to me. All signs are
pointin' to Princess Iris havin' the tourney in the bag
this year, too, so a complete unknown would be the
only real chance of an upset.

Mundane Mann... Looks like his first opponent in the
main tournament is none other than Annerose. I'd put
his odds at somewhere around nine to one.
C'mon, now. Let's not talk crazy here...
My dearest friend, Sir Po Tato.

I hope you are doing well, and please lend me some
money. I'm currently working to better myself with an
eye on the future, so please lend me some money.
Thus, please just give me some money...
Hahahahaha, no way! Hahahahaha...

(That guy I fought today was super fired up.
What was his name again...)

Qui...something. He reminds me of somebody, but I
can't remember who.
Huh?
You need something...?

Never thought you'd make it past the preliminaries.
Well done.
Eh, it was inevitable.

Yes. I can see now that I underestimated you. It's as
simple as that. But allow me to give you a word of
warning.
A warning...?

I've seen through your act. Don't think you can win
the same way you've been this whole time.
Heh...

I smirk and make to pass by Annerose unconcernedly,
all but saying that I don't have any more words to
waste on her.
(C'mon, please talk to me!)
Is something amusing?!
(Here we go!)
(Thanks!)
I have a warning for you, too...

No sooner do I say this that I remove the gauntlet
I'm wearing for just such an occasion and drop it at
my feet.
*thud*
The gauntlet makes a heavy noise as it hits the ground.
Wh-What the...?!

This fetter is a weight used to keep my power in
check... But playtime is over...
I drop the other gauntlet at Annerose's feet.
*gasp*
I walk off, leaving both gauntlets where they lay.
W-Wait just a moment!
But I don't stop.
I said wait!
She hurriedly puts herself in my path.
Don't think that you've won.
Why...even I can do this much!
Annerose cracks her neck.
It's unnecessarily fast.
...Huh.

I don't really get it, so I just step around a very
smug-looking Annerose and go on my way.
(What the heck was she trying to accomplish there?)
